They released RFTC in 1998, but Interscope turned their attention to higher-grossing acts and the band soon left the label.
This was followed by the departure of longtime drummer Adam Willard from the group in early 2000.
They released the EP Sultans and the album Ghost Ship in 2000.
Rocket from the Crypt regrouped in 2000, signing to Vagrant Records and bringing in new drummer Mario Rubalcaba.
Stamets continued to record and perform with Rocket from the Crypt, who released Group Sounds in 2001 and Live from Camp X-Ray in 2002.
